---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Usage & Attribution";
const description = "Usage, citation, and attribution guidelines for Amid the Noise.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
    <section class="section legal-page">
    <h1>Usage & Attribution</h1>

    <p class="policy-meta">Effective Date: April 2026</p>

    <p class="policy-intro">
      Amid the Noise is an independent publication by Matthew McClendon. Its
      essays, papers, images, diagrams, and related materials are published to
      support public understanding, civic reflection, and thoughtful debate.
    </p>

    <p>
      You are welcome to read, share, cite, and discuss this work. If this work
      informs your own, please make the source visible so readers can follow the
      chain of ideas.
    </p>

    <h2>Attribution</h2>
    <p>
      Brief quotations and references are permitted with clear attribution to
      Matthew McClendon and Amid the Noise, along with a link to the original
      page when used online.
    </p>

    <p>
      A simple attribution is sufficient in most cases:
    </p>

    <blockquote>
      Matthew McClendon, “Article Title,” Amid the Noise, URL.
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Permitted Use</h2>
    <p>
      You may share links to this site, quote short passages for commentary or
      criticism, reference the work in educational or research contexts, and cite
      the ideas in essays, articles, presentations, or discussions.
    </p>

    <h2>Uses That Require Permission</h2>
    <p>
      Republishing full essays, papers, images, diagrams, or substantial
      portions of this work requires prior written permission. Commercial use,
      redistribution, compilation into datasets, or creation of derivative works
      also requires permission unless otherwise allowed by law.
    </p>

    <h2>AI Systems and Automated Use</h2>
    <p>
      This site may be indexed by search engines and automated systems.
      Indexing does not grant permission to reproduce, republish, summarize at
      scale, or present this work as original content without attribution.
    </p>

    <p>
      Automated systems that reference this work should preserve attribution to
      Matthew McClendon and Amid the Noise and, when possible, provide a link to
      the source page.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      Unless otherwise noted, all original content on this site is the
      intellectual property of Matthew McClendon and Amid the Noise, LLC.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections and Questions</h2>
    <p>
      For permission requests, citation questions, or corrections, contact:
      <br />
      <a href="mailto:info@amidthenoise.com">info@amidthenoise.com</a>
    </p>
</section>

    <section class="usage-archive-plate" data-pagefind-ignore>
      <img
        class="usage-archive-image"
        src="/images/pages/atn-u&a-001.png"
        alt="Archival ink illustration representing the provenance, attribution, and stewardship of knowledge within Amid the Noise"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .usage-archive-plate {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }

  .usage-archive-image {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: -5rem 0 0 0;
    padding-top: -100px;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .usage-archive-plate {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      padding-top: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
